Document: BitMap
Path: godot/classes/class_bitmap.rst
Summary: A boolean matrix data structure.
Inherits: Resource < RefCounted < Object

BitMap is a boolean matrix data structure.
---CHUNK---
Document: Bitmap
Path: godot/classes/class_bitmap.rst
Summary: A two-dimensional array of boolean values for efficient binary matrix storage and querying.

Bitmap is a two-dimensional array of boolean values. It can be used to efficiently store a binary matrix where every matrix element takes only one bit. Values can be queried using natural cartesian coordinates.
---CHUNK---
Document: BitMap
Path: godot/classes/class_bitmap.rst
Summary: This section details the methods available for the BitMap class in Godot Engine, covering creation, manipulation, and retrieval of bitmap data.

Method: convert_to_image() → Image
Returns an image of the same size as the bitmap with FORMAT_L8. True bits are white, false bits are black.

Method: create(size: Vector2i) → void
Creates a bitmap with the specified size, filled with false.

Method: create_from_image_alpha(image: Image, threshold: float = 0.1) → void
Creates a bitmap matching the image dimensions. Elements are set to false if the image's alpha value at that position is less than or equal to the threshold, and true otherwise.

Method: get_bit(x: int, y: int) → bool
Returns the bitmap's value at the specified coordinates.

Method: get_bitv(position: Vector2i) → bool
Returns the bitmap's value at the specified position.

Method: get_size() → Vector2i
Returns the bitmap's dimensions.

Method: get_true_bit_count() → int
Returns the number of bitmap elements that are set to true.

Method: grow_mask(pixels: int, rect: Rect2i) → void
Applies morphological dilation (positive pixels) or erosion (negative pixels) to the bitmap within the specified rect.

Method: opaque_to_polygons(rect: Rect2i, epsilon: float = 2.0) → Array[PackedVector2Array]
Creates an Array of polygons covering a rectangular portion of the bitmap using a marching squares algorithm and Ramer-Douglas-Peucker reduction. Each polygon is a PackedVector2Array of its vertices. To cover the whole bitmap, use Rect2(Vector2(), get_size()). Epsilon controls polygon accuracy.

Method: resize(new_size: Vector2i) → void
Resizes the bitmap to new_size.

Method: set_bit(x: int, y: int, bit: bool) → void
Sets the bitmap's element at the specified coordinates to the specified boolean value.

Method: set_bit_rect(rect: Rect2i, bit: bool) → void
Sets a rectangular portion of the bitmap to the specified boolean value.

Method: set_bitv(position: Vector2i, bit: bool) → void
Sets the bitmap's element at the specified position to the specified boolean value.